bug.short_desc: Table font problem in mode "generate build"

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1200 small project (2 screenshots show what is the problem) Hi all, I'm using qx.ui.table.Table with qooxdoo 2.0.2 No problem when I use "generate source". The data, in the table body, look fine """
FDX
...
""" ==> we have the definition of the font to use for all the line But when I use "generate build" """
FDX
...
""" ==> we do not have the definition of the font to use for all the line ===> We have lost this font definition between "generate source" and "generate build"

I wanted to add that I have the same or very similar issue with my application.
One additional piece of information I can add is that using the build version, when I click on a cell to select a row, the table redraws using the correct font. If I perform an operation which deselects the row, the wrong font is again used for the table cells.
I have only noticed the wrong font being used in tables cells, not widgets such as tabs, buttons, labels.
The source version always displays with the correct font.

I have found that this bug is caused by my overridden function trying to access a private member variable in the base class. The 'privates' optimization does not allow this.
In our application we are extending qx.ui.table.rowrenderer.Default and overriding the createRowStyle() function. This function accesses the private variable __fontStyleString while building the row style string. Our copy cannot access this private function when the optimization is in force. BTW, this access did not produce a runtime error as the documentation indicates it should.
My solution was to rewrite my createRowStyle() to not need to access the __fontStyleSting variable. This may not work for others who wish to alter this functions behavior.
So I think we can close this bug.
